en_100885_0	Sri Lanka Signal Corps (SLSC) conducted a specially-designed training session on ‘Social Etiquettes and Working Place Courtesy’ for members of the Security Staff at the Open University of Sri Lanka (OUSL) on Wednesday (3) at the OUSL Staff Development Centre in Nawala.
en_100885_1	The request to this effect has been made to the Commander of the Army by the OUSL.
en_100885_2	The training session, designed under the close supervision of the Colonel Commandant of Sri Lanka Signal Corps was conducted by Lieutenant Colonel N.P.A Mendis of the SLSC.
en_100885_3	All members of the permanent Security Staff and the Chief Security Officer at the OUSL actively participated in the programme.
